<!-- General / Medical and Coaching Services -->
<section class="section section-alt" id="general">
  <div class="container faq-container">
    <h2 class="faq-section-title"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="faq-title-icon"><path d="M18 21a8 8 0 0 0-16 0"/><circle cx="10" cy="8" r="5"/><path d="M22 20c0-3.37-2-6.5-4-8a5 5 0 0 0-.45-8.3"/></svg>Medical &amp; Coaching Services</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>What is the difference between being a patient and being an EduCoaching client?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p><strong>Medical Services (Patient):</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Patients must meet Dr. Bluestein in person for their first appointment in Colorado or Wisconsin</li>
          <li>Dr. Bluestein can write prescriptions, order lab work, and order imaging</li>
          <li>Follow-up visits can be virtual for up to one year (patients must reside in CO or WI)</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>EduCoaching (Client):</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Clients can live anywhere in the world</li>
          <li>No travel is needed &mdash; all sessions are conducted online one-on-one</li>
          <li>Dr. Bluestein or Rebecca Gluck, PA-C provides information and guidance to work with your local healthcare team</li>
          <li>Prescriptions and lab work/imaging cannot be ordered in this setting</li>
          <li>Rebecca Gluck, PA-C is also available for EduCoaching sessions and may be a more affordable option</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>What services are offered by Dr. Linda Bluestein, the Hypermobility MD?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Dr. Bluestein is currently accepting new clients for <strong>EduCoaching</strong>, which combines personalized information with one-on-one coaching. All sessions are live, interactive video calls with Dr. Bluestein. EduCoaching is available worldwide through Bendy Bodies, LLC.</p>
        <p>She is also accepting a very limited number of new <strong>patients</strong> for medical services. You can join the waiting list by completing the patient intake form on the <a href="/services/">Services</a> page.</p>
        <p>Dr. Bluestein is also the founder and host of the <a href="/podcast/">Bendy Bodies Podcast</a>, featuring expert conversations on EDS, hypermobility, and related conditions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>What services are offered by Rebecca Gluck, PA-C?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Rebecca Gluck, PA-C offers <strong>EduCoaching</strong> sessions through Bendy Bodies, LLC. She brings specialized experience in Ehlers-Danlos syndromes, hypermobility spectrum disorders, and other complex chronic conditions from her clinical background in physical medicine, rehabilitation, and genetics.</p>
        <p>Rebecca may be a more affordable option for those seeking education and coaching support. All sessions are live, interactive video calls available worldwide.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>Are virtual appointments available?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Yes. Virtual appointments are available for EduCoaching clients and for some patient follow-up visits. New and existing EduCoaching clients can schedule through Bendy Bodies, LLC. Existing patients can schedule through the patient portal.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>What are the payment options?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Clients and patients are directly responsible for payment. We accept credit cards and Venmo (@Linda-Bluestein). Full details are available in the respective portals.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>How do we create an environment where a diverse range of patients and clients feel comfortable seeking care?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>We are dedicated to fostering an inclusive atmosphere, recognizing the potential disparities in healthcare &mdash; especially for chronic and complex conditions. Every patient and client is treated with respect, sincerity, and empathy, receiving considerate and tailored care.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Medical Services -->
<section class="section" id="medical">
  <div class="container faq-container">
    <h2 class="faq-section-title"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="faq-title-icon"><rect width="8" height="4" x="8" y="2" rx="1" ry="1"/><path d="M16 4h2a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v14a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H6a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V6a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h2"/><path d="M12 11h4"/><path d="M12 16h4"/><path d="M8 11h.01"/><path d="M8 16h.01"/></svg>Medical Services</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>Is Hypermobility MD currently accepting new patients?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Hypermobility MD accepts a very small number of patients, and you can join the waiting list by completing the intake form on the <a href="/services/">Services</a> page. Dr. Bluestein and Rebecca are accepting new clients for <a href="/services/#coaching">EduCoaching</a> through Bendy Bodies, LLC.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>What medical treatments does Hypermobility MD offer?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Current patients are evaluated at each visit and prescribed a comprehensive treatment plan which may include medications, supplements, physical therapy, and occupational therapy. Laboratory studies and imaging will be ordered where medically indicated. When appropriate, Dr. Bluestein also provides referrals to appropriate specialists.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>How do I know which medical package to choose?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>We offer three session options to fit different needs:</p>
        <p><strong>Gold Package</strong> (Least Complex)</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Designed for a single, specific, limited health concern</li>
          <li>Typically 90 minutes for the first appointment and 25 minutes for follow-up</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Platinum Package</strong> (Moderately Complex)</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Designed for patients who need a comprehensive review or have multiple related concerns</li>
          <li>Typically 150 minutes for the first appointment and 50 minutes for follow-up</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Diamond Package</strong> (Most Complex)</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Comprehensive evaluations, extensive assessments, or complex medical histories</li>
          <li>Recommended for most patients with EDS, HSD, POTS, and MCAS</li>
          <li>Typically 210 minutes for the first appointment and 90 minutes for follow-up</li>
        </ul>
        <p>More information is available on the <a href="https://hypermobilitymd.md-hq.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">patient portal</a>. You can also review our <a href="/assets/HMD_Policies_and_Procedures.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">office policies and procedures</a> for full details.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>Where can I find more details about the medical services?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>The complete policies and procedures for our medical services can be found <a href="/assets/HMD_Policies_and_Procedures.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Coaching Services -->
<section class="section section-alt" id="coaching">
  <div class="container faq-container">
    <h2 class="faq-section-title"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="faq-title-icon"><path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M22 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>Coaching Services</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>What is EduCoaching?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>EduCoaching is a unique process developed by Dr. Bluestein that combines personalized information with one-on-one coaching. All sessions are live, interactive video calls with Dr. Bluestein or Rebecca Gluck, PA-C, available worldwide through Bendy Bodies, LLC.</p>
        <p>Through EduCoaching, you receive information and guidance to help you self-manage your condition. You will learn how to advocate for yourself more effectively in healthcare settings. The Bendy Bodies team empowers you to receive better healthcare from your own medical team, coaches you through the health, dietary, and emotional aspects of these conditions, and provides specific suggestions for improving the quality of your life.</p>
        <p><em>Coaching services are for educational and informational purposes only and do not take the place of medical care. Prescriptions and lab work/imaging cannot be ordered in this setting.</em></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>What are the differences between the EduCoaching session levels, and which one is right for me?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p><strong>Bronze</strong> (20 minutes) &mdash; Personalized one-on-one coaching focused on a single issue.</p>
        <p><strong>Silver</strong> (45 minutes)</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Detailed review of 2&ndash;3 issues</li>
          <li>Review of up to 10 pages of medical records</li>
          <li>Discount code for supplements</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Gold</strong> (100 minutes)</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Review of complex, multi-system problems</li>
          <li>Review of up to 30 pages of medical records</li>
          <li>Complimentary follow-up call (up to 15 minutes) within 30 days</li>
          <li>Custom handouts designed by Dr. Bluestein</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Platinum</strong> (100 minutes)</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Peer-to-peer consultation with your primary care provider (up to 15 minutes)</li>
          <li>Access to Dr. Bluestein&rsquo;s trusted resources</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>Where can I find more details about the coaching services?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>The complete policies and procedures for our coaching services can be found <a href="/assets/BB_Policies_and_Procedures.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Professional Mentorship -->
<section class="section" id="mentorship">
  <div class="container faq-container">
    <h2 class="faq-section-title"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="faq-title-icon"><path d="m11 17 2 2a1 1 0 1 0 3-3"/><path d="m14 14 2.5 2.5a1 1 0 1 0 3-3l-3.88-3.88a3 3 0 0 0-4.24 0l-.88.88a1 1 0 1 1-3-3l2.81-2.81a5.79 5.79 0 0 1 7.06-.87l.47.28a2 2 0 0 0 1.42.25L21 4"/><path d="m21 3 1 11h-2"/><path d="M3 3 2 14l6.5 6.5a1 1 0 1 0 3-3"/><path d="M3 4h8"/></svg>Professional Mentorship</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>Who is professional mentorship for?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Professional mentorship is designed for healthcare providers, coaches, and movement professionals who work with individuals navigating complex conditions like EDS, HSD, POTS, MCAS, chronic pain, and more. Whether you&rsquo;re early in your career or an experienced professional looking for a fresh perspective, these sessions offer a supportive space to gain clarity, deepen your knowledge, and elevate your practice.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>What kinds of topics will be covered?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p><strong>Clinical mentorship topics:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Diagnosing and managing EDS and HSD</li>
          <li>Navigating complex comorbidities (POTS, MCAS, CCI, etc.)</li>
          <li>Improving patient care in under-recognized conditions</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Business mentorship topics:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Building a niche, mission-driven practice</li>
          <li>Ethical entrepreneurship and sustainable growth</li>
          <li>Finding balance in a high-demand field</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each session is tailored to your needs. You can bring a challenging patient case, questions about treatment planning, help interpreting symptoms or lab results, concerns about scope of practice, or guidance on growing your practice.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>Is this a medical consultation?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>No. Professional mentoring is not a substitute for medical advice or patient care. These sessions are intended for educational and professional development purposes only. Dr. Bluestein does not provide direct clinical recommendations for patients who are not under her medical care.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>How long is each session and how do I book?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Sessions can be 20, 50, or 80 minutes and are held on the coaching platform, Jane. You can book directly through the <a href="https://bendybodies.janeapp.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">coaching portal</a>, where you&rsquo;ll also find available time slots and payment details.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <span>Can I book more than one session?</span>
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>Absolutely. While a single session can be incredibly valuable, some professionals prefer ongoing mentorship. You&rsquo;re welcome to book sessions as needed, or select a package for longer-term support.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

